    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Therion Halask — Retired Aerdi Advocate</h2>\n<p><em>Caelith's Rel Astra correspondent. The party's gateway in Rel Astra and the procedural anchor for the Sereth indictment (Path 1).</em></p>\n<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>Mid-sixties. Aerdi, dark-skinned, white hair worn close-cropped. A long pale linen advocate's robe with the disused color-sash of a retired bench. Reading lenses on a chain. A heavy silver ring on his right hand bearing his old advocate's seal.</p>\n<h3>Combat behavior</h3>\n<p><strong>Will not fight.</strong> Yields. He has not been in a fight in forty-five years and has no intention of starting now. His value is in his procedural knowledge and his Aerdi commercial-court network; killing him closes Path 1 of Phase 4 entirely.</p>\n<h3>Statblock summary (CR 1/2, PB +2)</h3>\n<p><strong>AC</strong> 11 · <strong>HP</strong> 18 (4d8) · <strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft. · <strong>Init</strong> +0 · <strong>Passive Perception</strong> 13</p>\n<p><strong>STR</strong> 9 (-1) · <strong>DEX</strong> 10 (+0) · <strong>CON</strong> 11 (+0) · <strong>INT</strong> 18 (+4) · <strong>WIS</strong> 16 (+3) · <strong>CHA</strong> 16 (+3)</p>\n<p><strong>Saves:</strong> INT +6, WIS +5.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> History +6, Insight +5, Investigation +6, Persuasion +5.</p>\n<p><strong>Senses:</strong> Passive Perception 13. <strong>Languages:</strong> Common, Old Aerdi, Suloise, Yeomanry diplomatic cipher.</p>\n<h3>Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Procedural Authority.</strong> Halask's procedural pleadings are accepted by the Aerdi Commercial Court without further authentication. His sworn statements are admissible in any Aerdi or Yeomanry court.</li>\n<li><strong>Quiet Network.</strong> Halask maintains correspondence with eleven Aerdi commercial-court advocates, three Aerdi imperial-customs functionaries, and Caelith. He can request a procedural opinion or a deposition from any of them within five to fifteen days.</li>\n<li><strong>Reader of Filings.</strong> Advantage on Investigation checks involving Aerdi commercial documents, registry entries, or court records.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p><em>Blooming Rot, Part 2 — Phase 4.</em> See <em>Rel Astra NPCs → Therion Halask</em> for full profile and approach phrase.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
